and leans over. Partially digested curry fills her mouth and is spilled out into the once clear waters of the toilet bowl. How... nice. Gagging on the taste of her own stomach acid, she continues to throw up until her stomach is nearly completely drained of the food she had just eaten. Her body had rejected the pills? Impossible! She could barely feel her fingers tingling when she threw up, they barely started to work!! @#%$. Spitting into the disgusting water, she flushes it and stands. That was more than nasty. Nefertiti reaches for her toothbrush and loads it down with some toothpaste. They had some new mouthwash out that was supposed to eliminate the need for brushing teeth, and even had certain foods that took the place of brushing, but right now Nefertiti decided to do things the old fashion way and just brush. And brush she did. Brush and scrub and scrap like she had a damned OCD or something. Throwing up was the nastiest thing in the entire world. Just nasty. Oh so, nasty... Rinsing off the bristles she puts the toothbrush back in it's place and takes a deep breath. ~Hope they didn't hear me puke my guts out...~ Opening the door she steps back out into the smoke filled room. Was it just her or was Derek *always* getting lit? Someone bumped into her, she was too tired still to realize who but she muttered a few words in reply and kept walking. Smiling as she sees Mika, Nefertiti takes a seat on the ground near her, with her arm resting on the coach cushion. Her eyes look over at Devin. It had been awhile since he set foot in their flat. After he had that ‘discussion’ in with Jash she thought he wouldn’t ever come back. Nefertiti smiled, though her mind did not want to let her. With her legs crisscrossed she sits silently, her smile working it’s way from her delicate face. Her eyes jump from person to person as she twirls a toe ring on her right foot. ~I wonder if I’ll ever be as good at all that mind stuff as everyone else…~ with a heavy sigh she lays her head on the arm that rests on the coach. <br>
<br>
