<br>
Nefe was finally back, same with Jash, but Jerron was gone. He shrugged. Jash was concentrating on some little orb thingie. He remembered his Xtreme friend telling him about it, and how he could easliy break off from a Darkslide to a 1080 with no problems in the orb. He remembered telling Jash, &quot;Really now? Dude, what's it like to need some orb thing to go to your... world, or whatever? Must suck.&quot; Derek smiled at his knowledge. He could do almost anything with his mind, where others limited it. He could create his own universe, and stay there for years... Actually, he did that, but people thought he was crazy. Reminiscing the days &quot;behind the Wall&quot;, so to speak, Derek pressed the button on the remote again. The speakers started bumping out the classics; Pink Floyd, baby!<br>
<br>
He touched Nefertiti on the shoulder. &quot;Hey babe, you better?&quot;<br>
<br>
Her scowl was more than an answer. 0_0; Derek sat back on the couch, careful not to disturb Jash. &quot;Why do people limit themselves just from the chemicals in drugs?&quot; he pondered aloud.<br>
<br>
&quot;Why do you sell them the drugs?&quot; Mika shot back.<br>
<br>
Derek all but ignored the traditional comment. &quot;It's money. Besides, being in the stupor of hallucinogens or narcotics should *unlock* your mind, not hinder it. Why are people so god damned lazy? You'd think by now, people would strive for more than just...&quot; he waved his arm around the room, &quot;This. This pitiful existance, this pinnacle of human society we've worked ourselves to. People are content to let other people or things, like my special-grown hydrike ::grins::, do what they want for them. It's pitiful.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You do the same thing, Derek.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;How? Cuz I smoke hy? Cuz I grow it? Cuz I sell it?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Uh, duh!&quot;<br>
<br>
Derek sighed. &quot;I grow the best because I let my mind go, and figured out how. I sell it because I can, as I'm not lazy enough to have some low-income, low-risk, low-satisfaction job. I smoke it cuz I can. I don't need to. I've not let the drugs hinder me in any way.&quot; He put a finger up, &quot;And don't anyone give me yer *shitt* about levitatin. My mind don't work like that, you know it.&quot;<br>
<br>
Mika sighed, and, before she let Derek go on another long-winded spiel like he's been doing lately, she looked at her wrist, and said, &quot;Time to party.&quot;<br>
