Nefertiti smiles as Mika pulls her to the dance floor. She never had been much of a dancer, but when the beat was phat and the mix was good she couldn't resist. What little of the pills that got into her system before she threw them up had faded on their way to the club. She loved it there. If she had her way she would live in the dark atmosphere with the twirler's glow sticks as her only light. An ear to ear smile perminently sticks to her face as the songs roll on while she dances with Mika. Could life get any better? The neon lighting leaves a mysterious glow on her radiant face. It had been too long since she truly smiled. <br>
